robert lee bonaparte a retired vice 
president of boise cascade corp died saturday of heart failure at 
age 67 
he died at his home 
a newsprint and marketing specialist bonaparte worked for boise 
cascade for about 25 years until his retirement as a vice president 
in 1987 at the time of his death he was a senior adviser for the 
company 
in 1965 bonaparte cofounded schramsberg vineyards in 
californias napa valley 
