bonnie anderton was going to spend christmas day in the nations 
capital campaigning for the release of iraqs hostages including 
her husband she and 11yearold daughter jennifer had a petition 
to deliver to the iraqi embassy 
it was the nicest wasted effort ive ever made said mrs 
anderton whose husband richard was among holdouts at the us 
embassy in kuwait allowed to leave in time for the holidays 
just two weeks ago she and families around the nation wondered 
whether theyd ever see their captive loved ones again since iraq 
invaded kuwait on aug 2 theyd had mostly bad news or none at 
all 
he didnt think hed be home and we didnt think hed be 
home mrs anderton 40 said monday from larkspur colo 
thats why its so special just to be together 
theyre thankful at how things worked out for them especially 
compared with the nearly 300000 us servicemen and women in the 
persian gulf and their families despite the andertons good 
fortune its still a somber holiday season with the united states 
on the brink of war 
im extremely glad my husband isnt sitting on the 50yard 
line but theres still a tremendous problem to be solved mrs 
anderton said its far from over 
pete dooley never thought hed be out in time to sip champagne 
and sit around the christmas tree opening gifts at home in 
kentucky in a twinkling he went from hiding in iraqioccupied 
kuwait to freedom and the loving arms of relatives who had prepared 
for the worst 
we were looking for the long haul his mother kitty dooley 
said monday from hopkinsville ky we didnt dream wed have him 
with us that wed be calling out with joy 
