<TEXT>
single mother valerie bodon wanted to shower 
her four sons with gifts and cook a scrumptious christmas feast 
today but there was no money luckily she wasnt too proud to 
ask for help 
for mrs bodon who tries to make ends meet with food stamps and 
a 405 monthly government check the help came from a small 
indianapolis group that prefers to remain anonymous 
delivered to her door last week were about 30 wrapped gifts 
four stockings stuffed with candy fruit and other treats a 
miniature decorated christmas tree and two gift certificates from 
a supermarket and discount shoe store 
mrs bodon has been studying accounting at butler university so 
she can get a better job she was divorced three years ago while 
working as an accounting clerk a job that did not pay enough to 
support the family 
knowing she had virtually nothing to give her boys for 
christmas she went to one of the 14 community centers of 
indianapolis in november to ask for help 
the nonprofit agency which provided christmas assistance to 
more than 3500 families last year brings together people who want 
to help with those who need it spokesman ward beckham said 
shes trying to go to school trying to raise a family trying 
to keep her budget balanced said mike waddell her counselor at 
one of the centers she impressed me as somebody whos going to 
be a real success when she starts working 
many other families are in similar circumstances most are 
headed by single mothers trying to get by on welfare others are 
elderly people on social security 
the community centers of indianapolis help families when they 
are behind on their rent or utility bills or when the cupboards are 
empty 
at christmas the centers work with stores and groups such as 
kmart the fire department marine reservists supermarkets 
service clubs and the gas company which donate money food or 
toys beckham said 
affluent churches funnel help through the community centers or 
churches that serve the poor 
yet the churches and agencies can help only those who ask for 
it some children will have empty stockings because their parents 
are either too proud embarrassed or drugaddicted to seek help 
officials say 
a lot of children dont get the christmas they want a few 
dont get the christmas they need said cindy clements executive 
director of christamore house another of the centers 
with the extra help from her anonymous benefactors mrs bodon 
will be able to give her children more than they could have 
expected 
im just happy that somebody is doing this for me she said 
as long as the tree isnt bare on christmas then theyll be 
satisfied 
