there will be fewer fruit and what there is will cost more 
peters said 
inmporters of chilean fruit like los angelesbased david 
oppenheimer amp co expected demand for foreign fruit to increase as 
markets scramble to make up for local losses 
it was freezeofthecentury stuff said dave carman of the 
national weather service this is probably the secondcoldest 
freeze of the century we are dealing with extreme record cold 
since friday temperatures throughout the san joaquin valley 
citrus region had dipped to 20 degrees and below and were forecast 
to drop into the teens early today it was the worst freeze since 
1937 officials said 
navel oranges begin to show damage if temperatures fall to 25 or 
