<TEXT>
the armed forces appeared in control 
of this former dutch colony today after toppling the nearly 
3yearold elected government in what two former surinamese 
officials called a bloodless coup 
the dutch government today condemned the military takeover 
monday night and dutch tv said no one was arrested in the coup 
the takeover followed a dispute between president ramsewak 
shankar and longtime military chief lt col desi bouterse who 
had resigned earlier in the day 
there were no reports of shooting and shankars whereabouts were 
not known dutch foreign ministry spokesman dig istha said that 
practically all communication lines out of suriname were still cut 
