by bouterse 
in 1980 bouterse led a military coup that toppled a 
legitimately elected government in the small mineralrich country 
on south americas northeastern tip he ruled until elections in 
november 1987 which shankars front for democracy and development 
party won by a landslide 
relations between the government and bouterse have been strained 
ever since shankar began serving a fiveyear term on jan 25 1988 
with bouterse wielding considerable power by virtue of his control 
of the military 
in amsterdam netherlands a former highranking surinamese 
official who spoke with bouterse after mondays coup said the 
military had acted after the government reneged on a pledge to step 
down 
