damage 
the richter scale measures ground motion as recorded on 
seismographs every increase of one number means a 10fold increase 
in intensity 
an earthquake of magnitude 6 can cause severe damage in a 
populated area while one measuring 7 is classified as a major 
earthquake capable of causing widespread heavy damage 
