want to unite with moslem pakistan but others have called for a 
plebiscite to choose their future 
wani speaking from a hideout was quoted as saying kashmiris 
have become conscious of their rights and now they are ready 
to make any sacrifice for this cause 
in punjab simranjit singh mann said he was prepared to talk 
about selfdetermination for the wealthy farming state where sikhs 
have a bare majority overall sikhs are only 2 percent of indias 
880 million people 
mann was elected to parliament in 1989 at the head of the 
largest sikh faction but resigned his seat last year he is known 
to be close to some guerrilla factions but is opposed by others as 
too moderate 
extremists have killed more than 3200 people this year in 
punjab in the most violent12 months since sikhs launched their 
independence campaign in 1983 
another 1700 people have died in kashmir since the government 
began a crackdown on the separatist movement a year ago 
india has accused pakistan of supporting the guerrillas in the 
two border states with training and weapons islamabad says it 
provides only moral and political support to the secessionists 
press trust of india reported that army troops arrested a senior 
leader of the united liberation front of assam in what was called 
a major breakthrough in the governments searchanddestroy mission 
against the front 
so far about 1000 suspected front guerrillas have been 
captured since the offensive was launched on nov 28 but most 
leaders have escaped reportedly across the border to burma 
the front has been fighting a separatist campaign since 1988 
claiming the state was being stripped of its revenues from its rich 
tea plantations and oil fields 
at least two tea companies had closed their operations because 
of kidnappings and extortion before the government imposed federal 
rule and sent in the army 
