<TEXT>
oarsmen and history buffs 
rowed across the delaware river tuesday reenacting the christmas 
day maneuver by george washington and his troops that helped turn 
around the revolutionary war 
more than 15000 people cheered the arrival of the four wooden 
boats that carried 120 men in colonial costume from pennsylvania to 
new jersey 
at the bow of one boat stood james gallagher who has portrayed 
washington in the annual crossing since 1985 he wore a 
tricornered hat buff trousers a blue coat with gold buttons and 
a navy cape lined with red 
