and clearly it was the best christmas we ever had he said his 
stores had a 3 percent increase from 1989s holiday sales 
johnson said the weakening economy actually helped his home 
furnishings and clothing business as consumers traded down or 
bought less expensive gifts this year people that normally 
bought gifts at higherend shops came to pier 1 he said 
other retailers also saw evidence of consumers trading down 
at dayton hudson business was strongest at the firms target 
discount stores where sales rose about 2 percent macke said 
meanwhile sales fell at the companys daytons hudsons and 
